		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />mmhhh i think i got it.
<br />
<br />i didnt deleted the sram before i have soldered the new eprom(s).
<br />
<br />maybe this has caused the errors.
<br />
<br />a friend told me, that mario rpg uses the sram as ram... but 
<br />there was other data in it.. garbage data i think. then mario rpg now
<br />trying to access the sram .. it crashes. there is resist data
<br />in it.
<br />
<br />after i put it on my action replay... the arp deleted the sram.
<br />
<br />and now it works fine, without the action replay in it.
<br />
<br />
<br />allways remember! delete sram!
<br />
<br />
<br />sorry for bad english... its not really my lang <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />

		

